item.dc:creator: @relmitos relmitos
item.description:
@relmitos wrote:

To add an exception go to start > config > security centre. Scroll all the way down and click the Windows firewall icon.
A window will popup, in that window click on the exceptions tab. Once there click “Add port” and add 43594 for both TCP and UDP.

You should also add Java to the programs list.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: December 25, 2009, 08:02:22 am[/size][hr]A new router won’t solve your problem. You still have to port forward.
